bug.short_desc: gnome software shows not installed pkgs as installed
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1255435 Gnome-software window showing foxit as installed
Description of problem: Running gnome-software shows "foxit" as installed pkg, but this is really wrong: trying to launch this pkg fails, and trying to remove it, fails too! Installing it fails
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable)
gnome-software-3.22.5-1.fc25.x86_64 How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1.run gnome-software->productivity->all 2. 3.
Actual results: foxit is shown as runnable software
Expected results: foxit is not shown
Additional info: I installed only once within wine, but I removed it immediately.

Created attachment 1255436 strace if trying to remove foxit
Running gnome-software in remove mode for foxit under strace
Another experience: The alacarte package is shown is installed 3 times, but it's not installed!
Getting rid of the issue with a "rpm --rebuilddb" (with gnome-software-3.22.7-1.fc25.x86_64 too).
